[[Herblore]] is arguably one of the hardest skills to train on Ironman since collecting the herbs and most of the secondary ingredients can be slow and time-consuming. Therefore, it is advised to put the rewards of every [[experience lamp]] and [[book of knowledge]] into Herblore if possible. By the time all hard [[Achievement diary|diaries]] are completed, if making all potions obtained along the way, the player should have around level 67-69 Herblore, just enough to start boosting to make ranging potions.

==Early training: Quests==
{{Main|Quest experience rewards#Herblore}}

[[Druidic Ritual]] is required for unlocking Herblore. Afterwards, some early levels can be skipped by completing quests that reward Herblore experience. Completing Druidic Ritual, [[Jungle Potion]], and [[Recruitment Drive]] rewards in total 2,025xp, enough for level 13. Questing alone will grant a total of 9,350 Herblore experience, elevating a level 1 Herblore to 26, granting the ability to make [[energy potion]]s without having made a single potion before.

* [[Druidic Ritual]] rewards 250xp
* [[Jungle Potion]] requires {{SCP|Herblore|3}}, rewards 775xp
* [[Recruitment Drive]] requires [[Black Knights' Fortress]], [[Druidic Ritual]], rewards 1,000.5xp
* [[Zogre Flesh Eaters]] requires [[Big Chompy Bird Hunting]], [[Jungle Potion]], {{SCP|Herblore|8}}, {{SCP|Smithing|4}}, {{SCP|Ranged|30}}, rewards 2,000xp
* [[The Dig Site]] requires {{SCP|Herblore|10}}, {{SCP|Agility|10}}, {{SCP|Thieving|25}}, rewards 2,000xp
* [[Shades of Mort'ton]] requires [[Priest in Peril]], {{SCP|Herblore|15}}, {{SCP|Crafting|20}}, {{SCP|Firemaking|5}}, rewards 2,000xp
* [[Heroes' Quest]] requires {{SCP|Herblore|25}}, {{SCP|Quest|55}}, {{SCP|Cooking|53}}, {{SCP|Fishing|53}}, {{SCP|Mining|50}}, and many quests, rewards 1,325xp

==General information and tips==
Mid-level players may wish to kill [[Spitting Wyvern]]s for their high drop rate of 4-dose [[prayer potion]]s. This method obtains [[ranarr seed]]s, [[ranarr weed]]s, and prayer potions at a fairly quick rate.

A long-term method of achieving [[stamina potion]]s for the [[Player-owned house]] [[revitalisation pool]] is to always carry a clean [[torstol]] for the chance of a [[Jekyll and Hyde]] random event. Doing this significantly decreases the time required for higher tier [[Pool space|player-owned house pools]].

==Level 3+: Cleaning herbs, making potions/tars==
It is advisable to work towards having access to [[Managing Miscellania]] as early as possible, since it is one of the best ways to get herbs passively over time. Training [[Ironman Guide/Thieving|Thieving]] to high levels is a quick way to get coins for funding the kingdom; in addition to this, with high Thieving one is able to effectively pickpocket [[Master Farmer]]s for early herb seeds. When the kingdom is obtained, have 10 workers on herb farming at all times for the most effective yield.

After completing hard tasks of the [[Desert Diary]], [[Zahur]] in [[Nardah]] will make unfinished potions for 200 coins per potion (works with noted herbs and vials of water). [[Wesley]] will crush items that require the use of a [[pestle and mortar]] for 50 coins per item (also works with banknotes but does not require the diary completion).

