==Other methods==
===Level 80+ Hunter: Herbiboar===
{{Main|Herbiboar}}

At level {{SCP|Hunter|80|link=yes}} (and 31 Herblore), players can track [[herbiboar]]s on [[Fossil Island]], which yields herbs and a small amount of Herblore experience upon harvest.

===Bossing and Raids===
High-level players will get a notable amount of herbs and Herblore experience (from [[dark relic]]s and making potions inside the raid) from the [[Chambers of Xeric]]. Those with [[Craw's bow]] and/or [[Viggora's chainmace]] can focus on killing the [[Wilderness]] bosses [[Venenatis]], [[Vet'ion]] and [[Callisto]] as they rarely drop 100 noted herbs ([[snapdragon]], [[ranarr weed]] and [[toadflax]], respectively) as well as a generous amount of [[ranarr seed|ranarr]] and [[snapdragon seed]]s. Notably, [[Venenatis]] also occasionally drops 500 noted [[red spiders' eggs]].

==Sourcing ingredients==
Herblore ingredients come from three primary sources: farming, monster drops, and minigames (notably [[Managing Miscellania]]).

For farming, you can obtain seeds through [[farming contract]]s and pickpocketing [[Master Farmer]]s. You should be doing as many farming contracts per day as possible, they provide a lot of herblore and farming xp and are your main source of herb/tree seeds.

While training [[Ironman Guide/Slayer|Slayer]], you'll also obtain many grimy herbs and secondary ingredients.

===Herbs and herb seeds===
Low-level ironmen can get their starting Herblore supplies from [[Wintertodt]]. Alternatively, kill [[chaos druid]]s or [[flesh crawler]]s for their common low-level herb drops to train the first levels.

Pickpocketing [[Master Farmer]]s is the fastest method of obtaining [[ranarr seed]]s for [[prayer potion]]s, and it also yields various other seeds for Herblore experience. Players will need to have a very high [[Thieving]] level in order to do this effectively. Players stop failing to pickpocket Master Farmers at level 94 with the hard [[Ardougne Diary]] perk, or at level 99 when wearing the [[Thieving cape]]. It is recommended for players to have at least 71 [[Farming]] due to an {{UD|Fishing Skill Boss and Easter Event|update}} on the Master Farmer's herb seed loot table.

Doing [[farming contracts]] in the [[Farming Guild]] is currently the best method to obtain herb seeds at any levels. For more information, see the [[Ironman Guide/Farming|Farming]] section.

In addition to farming contracts, training Slayer is one of the primary methods of obtaining herbs and herb seeds, as many slayer monsters (most notably [[Nechryael]], [[Aberrant spectre]]s and [[Dagannoth]]s) frequently drop assorted types of them. Should one need herb seeds, complete Nechryael tasks in the [[Slayer Tower]] with melee instead of burst/barrage spells in the [[Catacombs of Kourend]] as [[Greater nechryael]] do not drop as many herb seeds in comparison.

===Farming herbs===
{{Main|Ironman Guide/Farming}}

Players will need to do herb runs frequently and consistently. Clean the herbs whilst running to the next patch to save time in future.

Always use [[ultracompost]] on herb patches to minimise the chance of disease, and to ensure the minimum amount of 6 herbs per seed when used along with [[magic secateurs]]. Herb patches cannot be protected by NPC gardeners, and seeds will typically be in short supply, so use the best compost possible.

[[Fertile Soil]] spell (requires 83 Magic) on the Lunar spellbook is particularly convenient for herb runs since it negates the need to spend time making ultracompost. However, getting an [[ash covered tome]] for unlocking the ultracompost version of the spell can take a while due to the Kudos requirement of the [[Volcanic Mine]]. When access to Fertile Soil is obtained, do herb runs whilst on the Lunar spellbook and use teleport tablets or Spellbook Swap for patches which aren't easily accessible without the use of the standard spellbook. Having a lunar or occult altar in a POH is recommended for switching spellbooks quickly, however the use of Moonclan Teleport or a house portal is also viable to teleport to Lunar Isle.

